      "text": [
        " هَكَذَا أَنْزَلَ اللَّهُ تَبَارَكَ وَ تَعَالَى لَقَدْ جَاءَنَا رَسُولٌ مِنْ أَنْفُسِنَا عَزِيزٌ عَلَيْهِ مَا عَنِتْنَا حَرِيصٌ عَلَيْنَا بِالْمُؤْمِنِينَ رَءُوفٌ رَحِيمٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473705\">H 15017</a> – A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Yahya Bin Al-Mubarak, from Abdullah Bin Jabalat, from Is’haq Bin Ammar, who has said:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>bu Abdullah</span><sup>as</sup><sup>ws</sup> has said: ‘This is how Allah<sup>azwj</sup>, Blessed and High Revealed it: <span class=\"ibTxt\">“<a href=\"/#/books/quran:9#h128\"><a href=\"/books/quran:9#h128\">[9:128]</a></a></span><a id=\"_ftnref34\"></a><span class=\"ibTxt\"><sup>[34]</sup></span><span class=\"ibTxt\"> Certainly a Messenger has come to us from among ourselves; grievous to him is our falling into distress, full of concern for us; to the believers (he is) compassionate”</span>. (Imam<sup>asws</sup> indicating the Tahreef in the Holy Quran) "
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "571. Muhammad, from Ahmad, from Ibn Fazzaal, who has said: Al-Ridha (a.s.) regarding: “<a href=\"/#/books/quran:9#h40\"><a href=\"/books/quran:9#h40\">[9:40]</a></a> So Allah sent down His tranquillity upon him and strengthened him with hosts which you did not see”. I said, ‘Like this?’ He (a.s.) said: ‘This is how we (a.s.) recite it, and this is how it was Revealed’."
        ]
      }
    }
